# Proposed Update — abstract-writing.md

**Source:** SkillTest R1.C case-abstract evaluation of nature-polishing.
**Status:** Draft only. Do not apply to
`/Users/mjm/MinionsOS/minions/roles/writer/skills/abstract-writing.md` until
the user explicitly approves the R1 synthesis port plan.

## What to add

The current `abstract-writing.md` already has the six-rung ladder. Add two
hard rules under the Procedure section.

### Add Rule: Explicit "Here, we show" main-result anchor

Current state (paraphrased from existing skill): "State the main result
(1 sentence, 'here we show' or equivalent)."

Proposed sharpening: Make this an explicit *required formula*, not an
"or equivalent." Specifically:

> **Main-result rung must use a direct verb formula** — `Here, we show`,
> `Here, we report`, `Here, we introduce` (for methods papers), or
> `In this work we ...` (last-resort alternative). The narrative
> formulation `We developed ...` / `We performed ...` is not acceptable
> for the main-result sentence; it reads as throat-clearing to a venue
> editor.

Evidence: SkillTest R1.C case-abstract. Baseline polished `We developed a
lipid nanoparticle ...` Candidate polished `Here, we show that a lipid
nanoparticle ...` User-equivalent rubric scored candidate higher on
claim-evidence completeness because the formula is venue convention.

### Add Rule: Bounded-implication closer

Add at the end of the rung 6 (broader context) procedure step:

> **Bounded implication.** Closing implication must name the species,
> scope, and system actually tested. A mouse preclinical demonstration
> closes with "establishes a non-viral route for CNS genome editing in
> mice and defines a platform for further preclinical evaluation," NOT
> "supports further evaluation in neurological disease models" — the
> latter implies disease-utility evidence the paper doesn't have.

Evidence: SkillTest R1.C case-abstract. Baseline closer slipped "in
neurological disease models" without disease evidence. Candidate closer
"defines a platform for further preclinical evaluation" stayed bounded.

## What to leave unchanged

- The six-rung ladder structure (broad context → technical background →
  study problem → main result → knowledge delta → broader context).
- The traceability requirement.
- The word-budget allocation.

## Why these are the only two changes

R1.C case-abstract showed the candidate beat baseline by +3 points (18 →
21 / 22) on three dimensions:
- Argument clarity / paper-type fit (paper type diagnosed first)
- Hedging calibration (bounded closer)
- Claim-evidence completeness (explicit "Here, we show")

The first one (paper-type-first) is in `apply-revisions` (covered in a
separate update proposal). The other two are local to abstract-writing
and warrant the rule additions above.
